We need to complete the proof for the theorem `zeros_outside_critical_strip_are_simple`. This theorem states that all zeros of the Riemann zeta function outside the critical strip (where the real part of the complex number is not between 0 and 1) are simple zeros. A simple zero means that the derivative of the zeta function at that point is non-zero.

